WEBVTT

00:01.419 --> 00:03.159
SAMUEL: Previously on Heroes.

00:04.630 --> 00:05.665
Get out of my head!

00:05.756 --> 00:06.836
This is a dream.

00:06.924 --> 00:08.460
No, it's not a dream!

00:08.593 --> 00:10.003
I came to get you
out of here.

00:10.094 --> 00:12.176
In the dream,
Emma, my friend,

00:12.263 --> 00:14.379
you save her
before she kills
thousands of people.

00:14.473 --> 00:16.213
You really think
you can get us
out of here?

00:16.309 --> 00:17.765
Let me see you try.

00:18.311 --> 00:21.849
HIRO: Charlie was my heart,
my world,
my happily ever after.

00:21.939 --> 00:24.726
/ did everything I could
to try and save her life.

00:24.817 --> 00:26.227
Where is Charlie?

00:26.319 --> 00:29.356
I'm the only one
who knows exactly where
your sweet Charlie is.

00:29.447 --> 00:30.482
Please help him.

00:30.573 --> 00:33.360
KENSEI: It is our intent
to prove that the defendant
abused his power

00:33.451 --> 00:36.659
to bend space and time
selfishly and repeatedly.

00:37.079 --> 00:38.330
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:38.497 --> 00:39.577
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:39.790 --> 00:42.577
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:44.670 --> 00:47.377
You think showing me
my dad's memories
is going to enlighten me?

00:48.591 --> 00:50.627
SAMUEL: You're afraid
she'll see the real you,
Bennet?

00:51.010 --> 00:52.875
CLAIRE: You brought a gun.
MR. BENNET: l was scared.

00:52.970 --> 00:54.176
That's the first time
you killed anyone.

00:54.263 --> 00:57.130
You actually thought
that I would turn on him?

00:57.225 --> 00:59.762
Claire Bennet
needs some time
to think about my offer.

01:04.899 --> 01:06.139
SAMUEL: It’s time
to gather the family.

01:06.234 --> 01:07.519
We’re moving on to
bigger and better things.

01:07.610 --> 01:09.191
It's gonna be
the greatest show
we've ever done.

01:12.281 --> 01:14.237
CLAIRE: Dad? Dad?

01:14.325 --> 01:16.065
MR. BENNET: (GRUNTING)
I'm here.

01:16.160 --> 01:17.195
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

01:17.286 --> 01:19.026
There's no signal.

01:20.039 --> 01:21.529
Claire, you okay?

01:21.666 --> 01:24.999
Yeah. You?
Yeah. Here, help me
get these ropes off.

01:26.170 --> 01:28.161
Is that a lantern
over there?

01:28.673 --> 01:29.833
(CREAKING)

01:29.924 --> 01:31.664
(GRUNTING)

01:33.678 --> 01:35.885
(PANTING)

01:35.972 --> 01:37.007
We're buried.

01:37.098 --> 01:38.508
How far down
do you think we are?

01:41.185 --> 01:42.391
Hello?

01:43.020 --> 01:44.681
Can anyone hear us?

01:44.772 --> 01:46.512
Anybody hear us?

01:53.447 --> 01:55.153
(CRUMBUNG)

01:56.284 --> 01:59.071
Help! Hello!
Can anybody hear us?

02:00.621 --> 02:02.236
Hello!
Anybody up there?

02:02.331 --> 02:04.071
Somebody help us!

02:05.376 --> 02:07.116
Help!
Can anybody hear us?

02:07.211 --> 02:09.702
Hello! Can you
hear us up there?

02:41.912 --> 02:43.743
(SOFT RUMBLING)

02:51.255 --> 02:52.620
(RUMBLING)

02:59.972 --> 03:01.257
(RUMBLING)

03:07.563 --> 03:08.678
(GRUNTS)

03:09.231 --> 03:10.732
(COUGHING)

03:15.905 --> 03:17.941
(PANTING)

03:22.703 --> 03:24.944
How long has
it been, really?

03:25.790 --> 03:27.576
Half a day, maybe.

03:28.584 --> 03:31.451
Feels like
we were in there
for years.

03:31.545 --> 03:33.376
(PANTS)

03:33.464 --> 03:35.295
Is your buddy Samuel
here with you?

03:35.424 --> 03:37.540
Came alone this time.

03:37.635 --> 03:38.624
Soto speak.

03:39.136 --> 03:40.296
And what do you want?

03:40.429 --> 03:41.885
Samuel asked me
to come here
and make sure

03:41.972 --> 03:44.884
your friends downstairs
aren't a problem for us.

03:44.975 --> 03:46.306
Guess that
means you, too.

03:51.941 --> 03:53.681
Sorry to break up
the love fest.

03:54.735 --> 03:55.724
(SIGHS)

03:57.154 --> 03:58.610
Come on.

04:00.491 --> 04:01.822
You're having doubts
about this.

04:02.785 --> 04:05.071
Look at you.
Come on, I can tell.

04:05.162 --> 04:07.153
You don't really
want to do this.

04:07.957 --> 04:10.198
What I want
doesn't matter.

04:10.793 --> 04:11.999
I don't have
another choice.

04:12.878 --> 04:15.085
Don't bother.
We got you outnumbered.

04:15.172 --> 04:16.161
(LAUGHS)

04:18.175 --> 04:20.507
MATT: You wanna
leave right now.

04:22.930 --> 04:25.342
Are you trying
to push a thought?

04:25.850 --> 04:28.592
All but one of us
are pretty thoughtless.

04:28.686 --> 04:30.017
(SIGHS)

04:38.070 --> 04:42.154
Tonight will be a night
unlike any other.

04:42.700 --> 04:43.906
Tonight,

04:45.369 --> 04:47.951
we change everything.

04:49.248 --> 04:51.455
For too many years,
we've been shamed
into believing

04:51.542 --> 04:53.032
we're second-class citizens,

04:54.712 --> 04:56.623
when the truth is,
we're king of the hill.

04:56.714 --> 04:58.250
CROWD: Yeah. Yeah.

04:59.049 --> 05:01.961
They should aspire
to be like us,
not the other way around.

05:04.638 --> 05:06.845
So I make this pledge to you.

05:08.267 --> 05:09.507
Tonight,

05:11.020 --> 05:12.635
once and for all,

05:12.938 --> 05:17.398
we pull back the curtain
and reveal ourselves
for who we truly are.

05:19.820 --> 05:24.063
After tonight,
we will be respected.

05:24.366 --> 05:26.357
(ALL CHEERING)

05:50.601 --> 05:51.932
(GRUNTS)

05:56.190 --> 05:57.680
(SCREAMS)

05:58.150 --> 06:00.141
(GROANING)

06:03.280 --> 06:04.486
MATT: Come on.

06:04.907 --> 06:07.523
Don't. Think about
what you're doing.

06:07.618 --> 06:08.858
(SCREAMING)

06:08.953 --> 06:10.443
Don't do this.

06:11.038 --> 06:12.448
(SCREAMS)

06:15.459 --> 06:16.790
Don't...

06:19.630 --> 06:20.836
PETER: Matt?

06:21.507 --> 06:23.372
Matt, are you okay?

06:23.676 --> 06:24.711
No.

06:25.553 --> 06:27.464
Here. Sit down.

06:28.305 --> 06:29.340
(GROANING)

06:29.431 --> 06:32.343
Okay, okay, okay.
It's just dislocated.

06:33.018 --> 06:34.269
Awesome.

06:38.148 --> 06:40.139
MATT: What the hell
is he doing here?

06:40.568 --> 06:42.104
(PANTING)

06:44.154 --> 06:45.940
(CARNIVAL MUSIC PLAYING)

06:55.916 --> 06:57.076
(IN SIGN LANGUAGE)

06:57.167 --> 07:00.079
Oh, there you are. Yes.
It's time for your solo.

07:03.090 --> 07:05.001
SAMUEL: How do you think
all the people
are gonna find us?

07:05.718 --> 07:07.333
You're gonna
bring them here.

07:08.721 --> 07:10.427
I told you,
you had a unique gift.

07:10.514 --> 07:11.879
Now it's time
to put it to use.

07:15.811 --> 07:16.800
What dream?

07:23.068 --> 07:24.729
Thousands of people
will die.

07:29.199 --> 07:31.110
He was right about you.

07:34.496 --> 07:36.407
You disappoint me, Emma.

07:36.999 --> 07:39.411
You can't force me
to do anything.

07:44.757 --> 07:48.215
lwould have
preferred you were
a willing participant,

07:49.053 --> 07:51.009
but these things happen.

07:52.431 --> 07:54.137
She's all yours,
Mr. Doyle.

07:54.224 --> 07:57.887
I've always
had a thing
for blondes.

08:08.113 --> 08:10.024
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

08:16.413 --> 08:18.699
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

08:53.450 --> 08:55.111
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

08:56.120 --> 08:58.281
Excuse me.
Hiro Nakamura?
Yes.

08:58.414 --> 09:01.702
The woman in Room 1106
asked me to give this to you.

09:09.133 --> 09:10.339
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

09:11.844 --> 09:13.709
l trapped him
in a nightmare.

09:13.804 --> 09:15.590
What the hell
is he doing out?
You did this.

09:16.014 --> 09:17.629
It's a long story.
It's a long story.

09:17.766 --> 09:19.757
But right now,
we need to know what
Samuel is planning.

09:21.103 --> 09:22.889
Thousands of people
are in danger, Matt.

09:22.980 --> 09:24.720
Get in his head, Matt.
Tell us what you see.

09:24.815 --> 09:27.101
Why? So you guys can run off
and be superheroes together?

09:27.818 --> 09:29.103
This is ridiculous.

09:29.194 --> 09:30.354
Peter, come on.
He's a monster.

09:30.446 --> 09:31.811
I can't believe
you'd actually trust him.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.112
If you want
something done...

09:36.201 --> 09:37.190
(SIGHS)

09:41.123 --> 09:43.739
Samuel's gonna show
the world his powers.

09:43.834 --> 09:48.077
New York City.
Central Park.
Tonight.

09:48.172 --> 09:49.662
What does he mean
"show his power"?

09:49.757 --> 09:52.749
He's gonna open up the ground.
Kill them all. Bury them.

09:52.843 --> 09:54.925
That sounds like
a plan I'd come up with
back in the day.

09:55.012 --> 09:56.343
You say that like
it wasn't yesterday.

09:57.848 --> 09:59.338
I'm not that
person anymore, Matt.

09:59.433 --> 10:00.843
I know it's hard
to understand.

10:02.895 --> 10:03.975
We got what we need.
Let's go.

10:04.062 --> 10:05.347
You're not
going anywhere.

10:05.439 --> 10:06.770
If you leave with Sylar,

10:06.857 --> 10:10.270
people are gonna end up dead
and that'll be on you.
I can't let that happen.

10:10.360 --> 10:11.645
Let's go.

10:12.237 --> 10:14.353
Come on. Let's go.
I'm not going anywhere.

10:14.490 --> 10:15.479
What are you
talking about?

10:15.574 --> 10:17.235
That would be me.

10:17.326 --> 10:19.282
See. I can still
push a thought.

10:19.369 --> 10:22.532
I told you, Peter,
I'm not letting him
out of here.

10:22.873 --> 10:24.363
(GRUNTING)

10:30.714 --> 10:32.250
We're too deep.

10:35.010 --> 10:36.466
No, we're not.

10:36.845 --> 10:38.346
We could dig our way out.

10:38.430 --> 10:40.261
Might take a while, but...

10:47.022 --> 10:49.183
We'll run out of oxygen
way before that.

10:49.274 --> 10:52.357
The more we dig,
the faster
we'll run out of air.

10:52.444 --> 10:55.936
Or more precisely,
the faster
I'll run out of air.

10:56.031 --> 10:58.397
Your lungs will
keep regenerating.

10:59.076 --> 11:00.737
What are you saying?

11:01.286 --> 11:02.696
It's futile.

11:03.247 --> 11:06.990
What do you mean "futile"?
We have to find
some way out of here.

11:08.710 --> 11:11.998
I think I know why Samuel
put you down here with me.

11:13.090 --> 11:14.546
So you could
watch me die.

11:20.180 --> 11:22.216
(PLAYS MELANCHOLIC TUNE)

11:29.022 --> 11:31.229
(CELLO PLAYING
THROUGH SPEAKERS)

11:31.316 --> 11:33.272
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

11:47.416 --> 11:48.826
Lure them in.

12:01.179 --> 12:02.635
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

12:04.349 --> 12:06.510
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

12:08.979 --> 12:10.264
Oh. Excuse me.

12:10.898 --> 12:12.104
My God.

12:13.191 --> 12:16.183
When I saw
the nurse's chart
said "Hiro Nakamura,"

12:16.278 --> 12:17.688
I couldn't believe it.

12:17.779 --> 12:20.270
It's been an awful
long time, Hiro.

12:20.365 --> 12:22.777
Ever since
the Burnt Toast Diner.

12:22.868 --> 12:24.278
Sixty-five years ago.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.409
Charlie?

12:33.712 --> 12:35.828
We have to focus.
We have to think
of something.

12:35.923 --> 12:37.288
Claire...
Dad, you have a plan.

12:37.382 --> 12:39.168
I know you have a plan.
What is it?

12:39.259 --> 12:40.999
(PANTING)
There is no plan.

12:41.094 --> 12:44.131
Now, I need to talk to you
about what you saw up there
in the House of Mirrors.

12:44.222 --> 12:46.429
Why?
Because you're gonna
survive this.

12:46.516 --> 12:50.304
If it takes a month,
you will get out of here.

12:51.188 --> 12:53.053
I'm not going to.
That's not true.

12:53.148 --> 12:54.513
That's not true.
Yes, it is.

12:54.608 --> 12:56.519
And there are things
that I need to say to you.

12:56.610 --> 13:01.730
What you saw up there,
all of it, it's all true.
But it's not the whole truth.

13:01.823 --> 13:02.983
Dad, you don't
have to do this...

13:03.075 --> 13:05.942
No. We are all products
of our own experiences,
good and bad.

13:06.036 --> 13:08.243
Everything that's
happened to me
has made me who lam,

13:08.330 --> 13:09.991
but it can't explain
what I've become.

13:10.082 --> 13:12.038
You're my dad,
for better or for worse.

13:12.125 --> 13:14.616
Don't protect me, Claire!
That's myjob.

13:14.711 --> 13:16.918
To protect me
from the rest of the world?

13:17.005 --> 13:18.506
Yes, exactly.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.291
(SOBBING) And that's why
you believe that
people like me

13:22.386 --> 13:23.717
can't live out
in the open?

13:24.763 --> 13:27.721
It doesn't matter
what I believe anymore,

13:27.808 --> 13:32.302
because the whole world
is about to find out
aboutyou.

13:34.064 --> 13:36.225
We can thank
Samuel for that.

13:37.234 --> 13:39.225
Maybe it won't be so bad.

13:39.987 --> 13:43.229
Maybe the world
is more ready
than you think it is.

13:43.740 --> 13:45.276
Things change.

13:46.493 --> 13:47.573
Sure.

13:48.036 --> 13:52.279
There might be curiosity
for a while,
but all it takes is one Sylar

13:52.374 --> 13:55.286
and then the pitchforks
come out and
all hell breaks loose.

13:55.377 --> 13:56.787
I've seen it.

13:56.878 --> 14:00.041
They will
turn on you, Claire.
lt's human nature.

14:00.716 --> 14:02.126
You're right.

14:02.551 --> 14:04.041
Things change.

14:05.387 --> 14:07.002
But people don't.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.678
Sylar killed your brother,
Peter. He killed Nathan.

14:16.773 --> 14:17.808
l've repented.

14:17.899 --> 14:19.514
Yeah. During the nightmare.

14:19.609 --> 14:21.600
Right.
'Cause that lasted all of,
what, a couple hours?

14:21.695 --> 14:24.027
Not to us, Matt.
That was five years.

14:24.114 --> 14:26.355
Look, you heard
what Samuel's planning.
We can stop him.

14:26.450 --> 14:29.533
I don't expect you
to understand what
happened in the nightmare.

14:29.619 --> 14:31.075
And I don't expect you
to forgive me.

14:31.163 --> 14:32.403
Good. 'Cause
that'll never happen.

14:32.497 --> 14:34.203
I've done so much wrong
to so many people.

14:34.291 --> 14:36.873
Just give me a chance
to redeem myself.

14:39.004 --> 14:42.087
Matt, I've been inside
ofyourhead,

14:42.174 --> 14:45.041
so I have a pretty good
idea of what it takes
to be a good person.

14:45.135 --> 14:46.591
Go inside mine,

14:47.304 --> 14:48.840
and you make the call.

14:56.730 --> 14:58.095
(GRUNTS)

15:15.665 --> 15:16.996
You see it.

15:19.544 --> 15:21.000
Right here.

15:25.217 --> 15:26.548
That wasn't your heart.

15:29.054 --> 15:30.669
I can prove it.

15:32.682 --> 15:33.888
Just give me a chance.

15:36.353 --> 15:38.389
You need to
trust us, Matt.

15:42.859 --> 15:46.067
Fine. Just get...
Get the hell out
of my home.

15:47.739 --> 15:49.024
Let's go.

15:49.366 --> 15:50.856
(DOOR OPENS)

15:52.369 --> 15:55.861
MATT: Now you are gonna do
exactly what I tell you to do.

16:28.780 --> 16:30.645
It's quite a crowd.

16:30.740 --> 16:32.651
They've all come out
to see us.

16:33.118 --> 16:35.279
See us do what?
Our acts?

16:36.788 --> 16:38.324
What else would I
be referring to?

16:44.421 --> 16:46.161
Those news cameras,

16:46.840 --> 16:48.330
did you invite them, too?

16:48.425 --> 16:50.837
The world needs
to meet us, Edgar.

16:52.220 --> 16:54.632
It's the biggest show
we've ever done.

16:54.723 --> 16:55.803
(GRUNTS)

16:56.266 --> 16:59.349
You seem nervous.
You aren't nervous,
are you?

17:00.437 --> 17:01.802
Excited.

17:01.897 --> 17:03.307
(PANTING)

17:04.107 --> 17:06.348
Tonight changes everything.

17:07.736 --> 17:09.442
For all of us.

17:13.617 --> 17:17.030
He was there waiting
as I left the Burnt Toast
that day.

17:17.120 --> 17:20.783
Some old man,
said he was a friend
of Samuel Sullivan.

17:21.291 --> 17:23.077
Put his hand
on my shoulder.

17:23.168 --> 17:26.877
Next thing I knew,
I was on a street corner
in Milwaukee.

17:26.963 --> 17:30.547
It was January 26th, 1944.

17:30.634 --> 17:31.714
Oh, no.

17:31.801 --> 17:33.211
It was cold.

17:33.803 --> 17:35.384
l was scared.

17:35.472 --> 17:38.134
I didn't know a soul.
And I missed you.

17:39.476 --> 17:41.341
And you lived
all this time.

17:41.436 --> 17:43.677
lgotajob
in a munitions factory.

17:43.772 --> 17:45.603
All the girls did
backthen.

17:45.690 --> 17:48.102
Did you realize it takes
108 pounds of rivets

17:48.193 --> 17:50.730
to hold the wing
of a P-51 Mustang
in place?

17:50.820 --> 17:54.062
Unless, of course,
you use the 14-gauge,
instead of the 16-gauge...

17:54.157 --> 17:58.275
Charlie, I'm so sorry.
This was all my fault.

17:58.370 --> 18:01.362
I led the evil Butterfly Man
right to you.

18:01.831 --> 18:04.868
It is because I loved you
that he sent you away.

18:19.599 --> 18:23.091
MR. BENNET: (WEAKLY) When
I said I was the product
of my experiences,

18:23.186 --> 18:25.677
I left out the most
important part.

18:26.523 --> 18:27.558
You.

18:29.567 --> 18:31.432
You came into my life,

18:32.320 --> 18:34.436
and you changed everything.

18:35.573 --> 18:37.359
The man you saw up there
in those memories

18:37.492 --> 18:41.326
could never have died
a happy man, but I can.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.285
Because of you.
No,no,no.

18:43.373 --> 18:45.739
Don't say that.
Don't say that.

18:45.834 --> 18:47.790
(SOBBING)

18:47.877 --> 18:50.584
Try to find a way
to forgive me, Claire.

18:50.714 --> 18:51.874
No.

18:53.550 --> 18:56.007
I don't need to
forgive you.

18:57.178 --> 18:59.009
I need to thank you.

19:00.181 --> 19:02.433
I am who I am
because of you.

19:04.894 --> 19:06.555
I love you.

19:09.399 --> 19:11.856
I love you, too,
Claire-bear.

19:13.445 --> 19:16.608
That's why I want you
to promise me something.

19:18.074 --> 19:19.860
That you'll hide.

19:19.951 --> 19:20.986
What?

19:21.077 --> 19:23.489
The world doesn't
have to know about you.

19:23.580 --> 19:27.072
You can stay in.
You can blend in.

19:27.584 --> 19:29.825
You can pass, Claire.
You know how to do it.

19:29.919 --> 19:33.582
Dad, we don't have to do this.
We can find a way out.

19:33.673 --> 19:38.417
I want you to promise me
you'll stay hidden, Claire.

19:38.511 --> 19:41.719
Please. It's my
dying wish, Claire.

19:43.099 --> 19:44.509
Please.
No.

19:44.601 --> 19:47.092
Promise me.
No.Dad?

19:47.354 --> 19:48.935
No. No!

19:49.606 --> 19:52.439
Dad? Dad, no! No!

19:52.525 --> 19:54.356
(GRUNTING)

20:21.805 --> 20:22.840
Tracy?

20:23.390 --> 20:25.221
I don't know what to do.
He's dying.

20:25.308 --> 20:26.297
Not if I can help it.

20:27.435 --> 20:29.300
Dad.
Noah.

20:29.437 --> 20:30.813
Dad.
TRACY: Noah.

20:31.481 --> 20:34.769
Tracy.
We have to get you
through 30 feet of dirt.

20:35.735 --> 20:36.975
You ready?
Yeah.

20:37.112 --> 20:40.070
Come on.
Come on.
Come on.

20:40.156 --> 20:42.317
(TRACY AND CLAIRE GRUNTING)

20:42.659 --> 20:43.899
You're gonna owe me one.

20:43.993 --> 20:46.951
He will, as soon as
we get out of here.

20:49.582 --> 20:51.413
I hope you can swim.

21:04.639 --> 21:07.972
(GRUNTING) Noah! Noah!

21:08.184 --> 21:10.049
(MR. BENNET COUGHING)

21:16.818 --> 21:18.183
(GASPS)

21:18.695 --> 21:20.276
(MR. BENNET GROANING)

21:21.114 --> 21:22.524
Dad, are you okay?

21:22.615 --> 21:24.697
Yeah. Tracy saved us.

21:24.784 --> 21:26.649
I know. I called her.

21:27.203 --> 21:28.283
MR. BENNET:
The carnival's gone?

21:28.371 --> 21:29.907
They're in New York.
Central Park.

21:29.998 --> 21:32.159
l lined up a chopper.
It'll take us
right into Manhattan.

21:32.250 --> 21:35.367
It'll be here any second.

21:38.673 --> 21:39.753
Where is she?

21:39.841 --> 21:41.331
She said you owe her one.

21:43.136 --> 21:44.592
We've gotta go.

21:48.683 --> 21:50.890
Don't beat
yourself up, Hiro.

21:50.977 --> 21:53.810
I would have waited for you,
but by the time you were born,

21:53.897 --> 21:55.228
l was middle-aged.

21:56.149 --> 21:59.391
I'm just so happy
I got to see you before...

22:01.404 --> 22:02.564
You're not well.

22:02.697 --> 22:06.940
The good news is,
that brain aneurysm
never bothered me again

22:07.035 --> 22:09.742
after your weird
doctor friend cured me.

22:10.246 --> 22:15.081
Unfortunately,
pretty much everything else
is about to give out.

22:20.548 --> 22:22.004
I can fix this, Charlie.

22:23.259 --> 22:24.715
FiX this?

22:25.595 --> 22:26.584
How do you mean?

22:27.931 --> 22:29.091
I can fix everything.

22:32.143 --> 22:35.101
I'm sorry.
Will you excuse us
for one minute?

22:41.611 --> 22:43.226
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

22:43.321 --> 22:45.277
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

23:23.194 --> 23:25.435
(CONTINUES PLAYING CELLO)

23:34.247 --> 23:37.660
He's done it.
He's brought in
thousands of people.

23:37.750 --> 23:39.832
This is gonna be
a massacre.

23:41.796 --> 23:44.333
We gotta find
the backstage area.
You know where it is?

23:44.424 --> 23:45.584
Yeah.
It's back
that way.

23:45.675 --> 23:49.042
All right. Let's split up.
You go that way
and I'll head off this way.

23:49.137 --> 23:51.503
Okay.
Claire, be careful.

23:53.433 --> 23:54.764
You, too.

24:01.733 --> 24:03.143
PETER: This way.

24:07.196 --> 24:09.107
Wait, wait,
wait, wait.

24:10.450 --> 24:12.281
The dream.
What?

24:12.368 --> 24:13.904
All these people
were all here.

24:13.995 --> 24:15.280
Like lambs
to the slaughter.

24:15.371 --> 24:17.623
It's not gonna
happen, Peter.

24:18.249 --> 24:20.581
Go find Samuel.
I'll save Emma.

24:22.503 --> 24:23.629
Peter,

24:24.672 --> 24:26.663
your dream said
I save her.

24:29.093 --> 24:30.549
Trust me.

24:37.310 --> 24:38.891
It's an emergency.

24:38.978 --> 24:42.095
Tell Hiro
he needs to get here
as fast as he can.

24:43.775 --> 24:45.936
Where do you think
you're going?

25:02.669 --> 25:05.285
Don't worry.
I've come to save you.

25:14.347 --> 25:15.587
(CHUCKLES)

25:18.351 --> 25:19.932
What brings you
to The Big Apple?

25:26.317 --> 25:28.103
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

25:38.162 --> 25:39.447
Everybody.

25:39.831 --> 25:41.992
Everybody, listen to me.
Please. Please. Okay?

25:42.750 --> 25:45.162
We need to get you
as far away from Samuel
as possible.

25:45.420 --> 25:46.751
You don't belong here,
Claire.

25:46.838 --> 25:48.954
Look, I know
what he told you
about tonight.

25:49.048 --> 25:50.128
That you're coming out,

25:50.216 --> 25:51.797
and that you're
gonna be able to
live out in the open.

25:51.884 --> 25:54.591
And trust me,
there is nobody who
wants that more than me,

25:54.679 --> 25:57.921
but this is not
your coming-out party.
This is his.

25:58.015 --> 26:00.142
Well, look who finally
came up for air.

26:00.226 --> 26:01.466
What are you
doing here, Claire?

26:02.353 --> 26:04.309
You're not part
of this family.

26:04.397 --> 26:06.012
You're right.
I'm not.

26:06.107 --> 26:07.392
But let me ask
you something.

26:07.483 --> 26:09.860
Does your family know
what you're planning
to do here tonight?

26:14.407 --> 26:15.988
Why don't you tell them?

26:16.534 --> 26:19.071
He's gonna kill
all of those people
out there.

26:19.162 --> 26:21.869
That's how he's gonna
introduce you to the world.

26:21.956 --> 26:23.992
Why would he
do that, Claire?

26:24.083 --> 26:26.415
He's given us all
new life.

26:26.502 --> 26:29.460
If he hadn't found me,
I'd still be living out
in that park.

26:29.547 --> 26:30.832
Homeless.

26:31.174 --> 26:33.165
(PEOPLE MURMURING)

26:33.968 --> 26:36.004
They know
the truth, Claire.

26:37.221 --> 26:39.177
Tonight is our night.

26:43.978 --> 26:46.720
I never wanted to
hurt your family, Edgar.

26:46.814 --> 26:49.021
Ask yourself if
that's true of Samuel.

26:49.108 --> 26:50.769
He killed
his own brother.

26:50.860 --> 26:54.728
I'm only here to stop him
from murdering
a lot of other people.

26:55.448 --> 26:58.235
Then you and l
have the same goal.

27:01.913 --> 27:04.199
lcan'tjust kill him
in front of the others,

27:04.290 --> 27:07.453
and you strike me
as the kind of man
with a plan.

27:08.169 --> 27:09.249
So what do we do?

27:16.469 --> 27:20.087
It's simple.
I'll be waiting
for you in 1944.

27:20.181 --> 27:22.092
When you pop in on that
snowy street corner,

27:22.183 --> 27:25.596
I'll take you back
to Burnt Toast Diner,
right where I left you.

27:25.686 --> 27:26.971
And I'd be young again.

27:27.063 --> 27:29.805
And we can finally
build a life together.

27:29.899 --> 27:31.184
Oh.

27:31.275 --> 27:33.061
That sounds nice.

27:33.444 --> 27:37.687
But, Hiro,
I already had a life.
I had a wonderful life.

27:38.324 --> 27:40.315
Sixty-five years
is a long time.

27:42.161 --> 27:43.617
Grandma!

27:43.704 --> 27:45.660
Hey, there, honeysuckle.

27:45.748 --> 27:46.954
Where's Mommy and Daddy?

27:47.041 --> 27:48.497
They're talking
to the nurse.

27:49.335 --> 27:53.248
Sally, this is
an old friend of mine.
His name is Hiro.

27:53.881 --> 27:54.996
That's a funny name.

27:55.091 --> 27:56.080
(LAUGHS)

27:56.634 --> 27:58.590
Hello, Sally.
Hi.

27:59.262 --> 28:03.471
Sally, go find Mommy and Daddy
so they can meet Hiro, okay?

28:03.558 --> 28:04.843
Okay.

28:08.813 --> 28:10.144
Hiro...

28:12.692 --> 28:15.274
After the war,
I married a wonderful man.

28:15.361 --> 28:20.025
We had four children.
I now have seven
beautiful grandchildren.

28:20.116 --> 28:24.860
We had a home, friends,
cherished memories.

28:24.954 --> 28:26.160
A life.

28:28.207 --> 28:31.074
If I were to go back now
and lead a different life,

28:31.168 --> 28:33.705
what would happen
with all of that?

28:33.796 --> 28:35.252
What would happen to Sally?

28:39.927 --> 28:41.303
ANDO: Hiro...

28:52.773 --> 28:54.479
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

28:59.947 --> 29:01.483
(INDISTINCT)

29:02.658 --> 29:03.864
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:51.082 --> 29:53.368
Doyle, I don't
want to hurt you.

29:54.085 --> 29:55.450
Just let her go, please.

29:55.544 --> 29:58.160
Since when do you
ask politely?

29:58.255 --> 30:00.246
A lot of people
are gonna die
if we don't stop this.

30:00.341 --> 30:03.925
Are you a shape-shifter?
Is that Dudley Do-Right
in there?

30:04.011 --> 30:05.217
You can't hold us
here forever.

30:06.055 --> 30:07.215
I don't plan on it.

30:08.766 --> 30:11.849
Just long enough for Samuel
to finish the show.

30:12.687 --> 30:14.473
Isn't that right, Em?

30:15.564 --> 30:16.644
Oh.

30:16.732 --> 30:18.814
(WHlSPERlNG)
I don't think she heard me.

30:22.655 --> 30:24.236
(SCREAMS)

30:26.117 --> 30:27.573
Are you okay?

30:28.911 --> 30:30.447
(GRUNTING)

30:30.538 --> 30:33.029
Sylar, please.
Listen to me.

30:33.124 --> 30:34.455
(CHOKING)

30:34.542 --> 30:36.453
Please.
Samuel made me do it.

30:36.544 --> 30:37.579
Really?

30:38.754 --> 30:40.494
Because I thought you were
the puppet master.

30:40.589 --> 30:44.298
Come on. What do you care
about this girl, anyway?

30:44.385 --> 30:47.092
I am here to save her.

30:47.972 --> 30:49.553
That's not you.

30:50.307 --> 30:51.558
You're like me.

30:51.642 --> 30:52.802
No.

30:55.688 --> 30:57.224
I'm a hero.

31:03.904 --> 31:06.520
You think you're here
to save them, Claire,
but they don't need saving.

31:06.615 --> 31:08.116
They know what
I've done for them.

31:08.200 --> 31:11.237
Do they know
that you gain
your strength from them?

31:11.328 --> 31:13.193
You are the source
of his power.

31:13.289 --> 31:15.325
Without you,
he is nothing.

31:15.416 --> 31:18.908
That's why Joseph was
keeping this family
small for all those years,

31:19.003 --> 31:21.995
because he knew.
He knew how powerful
Samuel could be.

31:22.089 --> 31:25.707
That he would lose control,
just like he did
when he buried that town.

31:25.801 --> 31:29.589
But you all walk away now,
and he will be weak.

31:29.680 --> 31:32.342
He will be ordinary.
He will be nothing.

31:32.433 --> 31:34.469
I think we've all
heard enough.
Am I right?

31:35.102 --> 31:38.890
He's using you, and that's
what Joseph was trying
to keep from happening.

31:38.981 --> 31:41.313
But why don't you tell them
what you did to stop him?

31:41.400 --> 31:44.312
That's enough.
He killed him.
He killed his own brother.

31:44.653 --> 31:46.359
(PEOPLE MURMURING)

31:49.408 --> 31:50.397
(WHIMPERS)

31:55.331 --> 31:57.162
You think they're going
to believe you over me?

31:59.001 --> 32:00.832
They'd be lost without me.

32:05.633 --> 32:07.715
There's not one person here
who thinks I'm capable

32:07.802 --> 32:09.042
of murdering my own brother.

32:10.387 --> 32:11.513
There's one, actually.

32:14.266 --> 32:15.767
Make that two.

32:17.603 --> 32:18.843
Lydia told me
everything.

32:19.688 --> 32:22.851
Well, she's not here
to confirm that now,
is she?

32:23.359 --> 32:24.769
Because he killed her.

32:24.860 --> 32:26.020
That's a lie.

32:27.905 --> 32:29.190
Isn't it?

32:31.242 --> 32:32.823
Tell the truth, Samuel.

32:35.663 --> 32:38.450
You had me kill Lydia.

32:41.544 --> 32:42.704
I did no such thing.

32:42.795 --> 32:45.377
You blamed it on me
to justify what
you're gonna do tonight.

32:46.132 --> 32:48.965
What? You're gonna believe him
after all I've done for you?

32:49.051 --> 32:53.044
I know I can't stay
in this family after
killing one of our own.

32:54.098 --> 32:56.180
But he has to be stopped.

32:57.560 --> 32:59.721
It's up to all of you.

32:59.812 --> 33:02.224
Claire's right.
You walk away
and he's powerless.

33:04.400 --> 33:05.640
It's over, Samuel.

33:06.152 --> 33:08.939
Come on.
Let's get out of here.

33:11.448 --> 33:13.029
Wait, wait, wait.
Where're you going?

33:15.035 --> 33:17.822
SAMUEL:
Don't you see?
You're victims.

33:19.290 --> 33:21.576
All of you.
Like Joseph.

33:24.920 --> 33:26.911
Run as fast as you can.

33:27.756 --> 33:29.917
You'll never get far enough!

33:32.261 --> 33:34.252
Ladies and gentlemen!
You want a show?

33:34.346 --> 33:36.132
Yeah!
Yeah!

33:36.307 --> 33:37.296
(CROWD CHEERING)

33:48.694 --> 33:51.436
Well, this is
the greatest show on Earth!

33:51.530 --> 33:52.736
(CROWD CHEERING)

34:00.539 --> 34:02.279
(CROWD CLAMORING)

34:07.379 --> 34:09.335
(CROWD SCREAMING)

34:16.972 --> 34:17.961
We're too close to him.

34:18.057 --> 34:21.140
Go! We need to get
as far away as possible.

34:48.671 --> 34:49.956
(GRUNTS)

34:53.175 --> 34:54.756
You seem to have
found my power.

34:55.511 --> 34:56.842
It's funny
how that works, huh?

34:59.848 --> 35:02.339
I'm not gonna let you
hurt anyone now.

35:05.896 --> 35:09.434
Peter, you of all people
should know
they have to fear us.

35:11.277 --> 35:13.393
That's the only way
they'll respect us.

35:13.779 --> 35:15.644
All you've ever
wanted is respect.

35:16.365 --> 35:19.607
We both know
what it's like to live in
the shadow of a brother.

35:19.702 --> 35:22.694
Joseph destroyed
my potential, kept me down.

35:22.788 --> 35:24.619
Just like your brother.

35:28.377 --> 35:31.710
My brother didn't
let me down.
He built me up.

35:44.059 --> 35:46.550
Hiro. You need to
teleport everyone
out of here.

35:46.979 --> 35:48.059
All of you?

35:48.147 --> 35:49.887
We need to try.
Everyone.

35:49.982 --> 35:51.938
There are so many.

35:52.776 --> 35:54.107
They all have to be touching.

35:54.445 --> 35:57.232
You heard him.
Everybodyjoin hands.

35:57.906 --> 35:59.066
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

35:59.742 --> 36:01.903
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

36:06.957 --> 36:09.573
I'll stay,
take care of Samuel.

36:16.467 --> 36:19.300
One, two, three!

36:21.638 --> 36:22.923
(PANTING)

36:23.015 --> 36:24.721
(RUMBLlNG STOPS)

36:24.808 --> 36:26.059
(GRUNTS)

36:33.942 --> 36:36.558
So, how does it feel
to be ordinary?

36:39.656 --> 36:41.396
(HUFFING)

36:42.159 --> 36:44.024
Where'd they all go?

36:47.623 --> 36:50.740
They can't have all left.
They're here somewhere.

36:51.627 --> 36:53.037
(GROANS)

36:57.299 --> 36:59.130
You can't leave me.

37:04.306 --> 37:05.807
You cowards!

37:11.397 --> 37:13.137
Where are you?

37:18.153 --> 37:19.859
Come back here!

37:19.947 --> 37:21.778
(PANTING)

37:23.826 --> 37:25.987
You're nothing without me!

37:33.710 --> 37:35.120
I gotta say,

37:35.754 --> 37:37.710
I never liked carnivals.

37:38.090 --> 37:39.079
Yup.

37:39.174 --> 37:41.916
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

38:09.204 --> 38:10.865
Are you okay?

38:13.584 --> 38:15.700
There was a man
named Doyle.

38:16.879 --> 38:18.085
He made me play.

38:18.172 --> 38:19.457
Doyle?

38:20.090 --> 38:23.082
Your friend
took care of him.

38:29.933 --> 38:31.264
(GASPS)

38:34.354 --> 38:35.389
What do you think?

38:41.111 --> 38:42.487
I like it.

38:45.824 --> 38:46.904
ls everyone safe?

38:46.992 --> 38:48.323
Yeah. Hiro's taking
care of them.

38:48.410 --> 38:49.946
They'll be fine.

38:53.582 --> 38:56.745
Who's taking Samuel?
Is it a new company?

38:57.336 --> 39:00.453
Old one.
Lauren called in
some favors.

39:00.923 --> 39:02.959
What's she telling them?

39:03.091 --> 39:05.503
There was
a gas main rupture.
CLAIRE: Of course there was.

39:05.594 --> 39:07.835
And all the other stuff,
the flying, the rumbling,

39:07.930 --> 39:11.514
all just special effects
put on by a very gifted
showman.

39:12.434 --> 39:14.516
You still can't see it,
can you?

39:14.603 --> 39:15.763
See what?

39:15.854 --> 39:16.889
The future.

39:17.481 --> 39:20.348
One where we all
get to live out
in the open.

39:20.442 --> 39:23.024
Claire, you know
how I feel about this.

39:23.111 --> 39:25.568
How long can we keep
this under wraps?

39:26.949 --> 39:29.281
Excuse me.
You were witnesses.
What happened?

39:30.118 --> 39:31.324
l have no comment.

39:31.453 --> 39:34.320
Can you tell us
what you saw here tonight?

39:34.456 --> 39:36.071
MALE REPORTER:
Come on. You must
have seen something.

39:36.166 --> 39:37.155
What he said.

39:37.626 --> 39:39.287
(CAMERA CLICKING)

39:41.463 --> 39:43.704
FEMALE REPORTER: Miss, please.
You have to have
seen something.

39:43.799 --> 39:44.879
MALE REPORTER:
Are you sure, Miss?

39:44.967 --> 39:47.379
You look like
you wanna say something.

39:48.136 --> 39:50.092
Actually, I do
have something to say.

39:50.180 --> 39:51.465
Claire.

39:53.642 --> 39:55.098
You're right.

39:55.894 --> 39:57.430
People don't change.

40:04.361 --> 40:06.727
You wanna know
what really happened
here tonight?

40:09.116 --> 40:10.981
Keep the cameras on me.

40:13.203 --> 40:14.534
FEMALE REPORTER:
Stay with her.
Don't lose her.

40:14.621 --> 40:15.656
Claire.

40:15.747 --> 40:17.612
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

40:20.460 --> 40:21.836
MR. BENNET: Claire.

40:23.630 --> 40:25.336
FEMALE REPORTER:
You getting this?

40:29.511 --> 40:31.126
What is she doing?

40:32.514 --> 40:34.050
Breaking my heart.

40:37.019 --> 40:38.350
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

40:38.437 --> 40:40.268
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

40:46.361 --> 40:48.272
It's amazing, Peter.

40:49.156 --> 40:51.397
What is?
When I saved her,

40:52.159 --> 40:53.444
I didn't have
a thought for myself.

40:53.535 --> 40:56.368
I could have killed Doyle,
but I didn't.

40:56.455 --> 40:59.618
It felt good.
It felt right.

40:59.708 --> 41:02.450
What the hell does
she think she's doing?

41:03.337 --> 41:05.498
She's gonna
change everything.

41:06.340 --> 41:07.830
That's right.

41:10.427 --> 41:12.509
It's a brave new world.

41:34.993 --> 41:36.949
(REPORTERS SCREAMING)

41:38.789 --> 41:40.654
(REPORTERS EXCLAIM)

41:46.129 --> 41:47.505
(GRUNTS)

41:49.383 --> 41:53.046
My name is Claire Bennet.
And this is attempt number...

41:53.345 --> 41:55.006
(LAUGHS)

41:55.097 --> 41:56.712
lguess
l've kind of lost count.

42:02.229 --> 42:03.344
(SlGHS)
